briefdescription.para: type definition for a locking object container

detaileddescription.para: Locking object are used to protect a resource from mutual accesses of two or more threads. The locking object should support re-entrant locks by a signal thread. This object is generally implemented by mutex semaphore

simplesect.para: On each porting or platform the type could be whatever is needed - integer, structure etc.

briefdescription.para: type definition for a sync object container

detaileddescription.para: Sync object is object used to synchronize between two threads or thread and interrupt handler. One thread is waiting on the object and the other thread send a signal, which then release the waiting thread. The signal must be able to be sent from interrupt context. This object is generally implemented by binary semaphore or events.

simplesect.para: On each porting or platform the type could be whatever is needed - integer, structure etc.

briefdescription.para: type definition for a spawn entry callback

detaileddescription.para: the spawn mechanism enable to run a function on different context. This mechanism allow to transfer the execution context from interrupt context to thread context or changing the context from an unknown user thread to general context. The implementation of the spawn mechanism depends on the user's system requirements and could varies from implementation of serialized execution using single thread to creating thread per call

simplesect.para: The stack size of the execution thread must be at least of TBD bytes!
